.TH HSH 1 "April 2026" "1.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.br
.B echo
.I "command"
|
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX command line interpreter written in C, built as part of the
Holberton School curriculum.
It reads commands from standard input and executes them.
It supports both interactive and non-interactive modes.

.SH USAGE

.SS Interactive mode
Launch the shell and type commands directly:

.nf
$ ./hsh
$ ls
$ /bin/ls
$ exit
.fi

.SS Non-interactive mode
Pipe commands into the shell:

.nf
$ echo "ls" | ./hsh
$ echo "/bin/ls -l" | ./hsh
$ cat script.txt | ./hsh
.fi

.SH BUILTINS

The following built-in commands are supported:

.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell with status 0.

.TP
.B env
Print all environment variables to standard output, one per line.

.SH EXIT STATUS

.TP
.B 0
Success — the command executed without error.

.TP
.B 127
Command not found — the given command could not be located in
.BR PATH .

.TP
.B 1
Execution failure — the command was found but
.BR execve (2)
failed.

.SH COMPILATION

.nf
gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic -std=gnu89 *.c -o hsh
.fi

.SH MEMORY CHECK (VALGRIND)

To check for memory leaks:

.nf
valgrind --leak-check=full --show-leak-kinds=all \\
         --track-origins=yes ./hsh
.fi

.SH FEATURES

.IP \(bu 2
Displays a prompt and waits for user input (interactive mode)
.IP \(bu 2
Executes commands using their full path (e.g.
.BR /bin/ls )
.IP \(bu 2
Searches for commands in the directories listed in
.B PATH
.IP \(bu 2
Handles end-of-file (Ctrl+D) gracefully
.IP \(bu 2
Supports the
.B env
and
.B exit
built-in commands
.IP \(bu 2
Works in non-interactive (piped) mode

.SH LIMITATIONS

.IP \(bu 2
No support for pipes
.RB ( | )
.IP \(bu 2
No support for redirections
.RB ( > ,
.BR < ,
.BR >> )
.IP \(bu 2
No support for semicolons or command chaining
.IP \(bu 2
No support for quotes or escape characters
.IP \(bu 2
No support for environment variable expansion
.RB ( $VAR )
.IP \(bu 2
No history, no tab-completion

.SH FILES

.TP
.B main.c
Entry point of the shell.

.TP
.B shell.c
String splitting and command execution logic.

.TP
.B find_path.c
PATH resolution — searches for the full path of a command.

.TP
.B builtins.c
Built-in commands:
.B exit
and
.BR env .

.TP
.B env.c
Environment variable printing helper.

.TP
.B main.h
Header file — function prototypes and includes.

